  "serviceNotes": {
    "engine oil": "Fiat’s EU service schedule for 500 TwinAir / Fire / Hybrid petrol engines specifies maintenance including oil and filter at 15,000 km or 12 months (whichever first) in the owner’s service booklet for European markets.",
    "cabin filter": "Pollen filter is replaced at the periodic maintenance interval alongside other routine checks.",
    "air filter": "Engine air filter replacement typically follows every second oil service on many Fiat small-car EU programmes (~30,000 km)—confirm in your maintenance plan.",
    "spark plugs": "Petrol engines list spark plug renewal at extended intervals in Fiat maintenance tables; 60,000 km is typical for four-valve Fire/TwinAir families—verify engine code.",
    "timing belt": "Where a timing belt is fitted (some variants), specialist mechanics often plan replacement near 120,000 km or earlier by age—chain-equipped engines do not apply.",
    "coolant flush": "Long-life coolant still ages; exchange around 120,000 km protects the small turbo cooling circuit on newer variants.",
    "brake fluid": "Brake fluid is hygroscopic and absorbs moisture over time, reducing its boiling point and braking effectiveness. Replacement is time-based, not distance-based — typically every 2 years regardless of mileage.",
    "check brake pads": "Brake system inspection is performed at each scheduled service as specified in the Fiat maintenance booklet."
  },
